quran[7]{c,v,t}:
  17,94,"Nothing prevents people from having iman when guidance comes to them but the fact that they say, ´Has Allah sent a human being as Messenger?´"
  17,95,"Say: ´If there had been angels on the earth going about in peace, We would have sent down to them an angel from heaven as Messenger.´"
  17,96,"Say: ´Allah is a sufficient witness between me and you. He is certainly aware of and sees His slaves.´"
  17,97,"Whoever Allah guides is truly guided. But as for those He leads astray, you will not find any protectors for them apart from Him. We will gather them on the Day of Rising, flat on their faces, blind, dumb and deaf. Their shelter will be Hell. Whenever the Blaze dies down, We will increase it for them"
  17,98,"That is their repayment for rejecting Our Signs and saying, ´What, when we are bones and crumbled dust, will we then be raised up as a new creation?´"
  17,99,"Do they not see that Allah, Who created the heavens and earth, has the power to create the like of them, and has appointed fixed terms for them of which there is no doubt? But the wrongdoers still spurn anything but kufr"
  17,100,"Say: ´Even if you possessed the vast storehouses of my Lord´s mercy, you would still hold back, fearing they would run out.´"